problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/find-pivot-index/description/?submissionId=2045268712

Intuition
The most important thing to understand is , at any index i , left : prefix sum will be written as , a[0] + a[1] + a[2] + ..... + a[i-1] , similarly right : suffix sum will be written as a[i+1] + a[i+2] + ....... + a[n-1]
so the main understanding is left + a[i] + right = total sum of that array.
hence right = total - left - a[i]

Approach
we know for index 0 the prefix sum will be zero so initalize left = 0
calaculate total sum of the array, for every index starting from 1 , update left by increasing a[i-1] , calculate right , check whether left == right , return the index when left and right are at equilibrium .

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Space complexity:
O(1)
Code
class Solution:
    def pivotIndex(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        left = total = 0
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            total += nums[i]
        
        if total - nums[0] == 0:
            return 0
        
        for i in range(1,len(nums)):
            left += nums[i-1]
            right = total - left - nums[i]
            if left == right:
                return i
        
        return -1
        
